The top K related problems are a common category of problems that involve finding the K largest or smallest elements in a collection of data.
These problems can be solved using max heap as it allows us to efficiently retrieve the largest element in a collection.
In Java its called PriorityQueue and in Python its called heapq.

Steps to identify if a problem is a top K problem or will require a min Heap or max Heap -
- Use a heap when you need to repeatedly access/remove the smallest or largest element efficiently
- Look for keywords -
    k smallest
    k largest
    top k
    minimum/maximum repeatedly
    closest
    merge

